{
  font: {
    bold: true,
    size: 11,
    color: { argb: 'FFFF0000' },
    name: '宋体',
    family: 3,
    charset: 134,
    scheme: 'minor'
  },
  border: {},
  fill: {
    type: 'pattern',
    pattern: 'solid',
    fgColor: { argb: 'FFFFFF00' },
    bgColor: { indexed: 64 }
  },
  alignment: { vertical: 'middle' }
}
```

Your font color is font.color.argb

The cell fill color is fill.fgColor.argb

These are in argb format, and switching to rgb means removing the first two digits, for example

FFFF0000 -> FF0000  red

FFFFFF00 -> FFFF00  yellow

